ation with wordplay, grammar, and stylistics that dominated discussions of poetry in al-Sanhūrī's day and shedding light on the literature of this understudied era.A bilingual Arabic-English edition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aArabic poetryy1258-1800xHistory and criticismvEarly works to 1800. 0aArabic poetryzEgyptxHistory and criticismvEarly works to 1800. 0aCountry life in literature. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh1 aDavies, Humphrey, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479890781.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479890781423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479890781/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles